# Festag — auth long-text expand popup

When an **under-title** auth field (Dev username „Benutzer eingeben“, workspace name while editing, similar hero inputs) becomes **too long** for the compact 32px line:

## Behavior

1. Open a **small horizontal popup**, centered on the overall auth surface (`.dl-panel` / `.al-signin`).
2. Show the **full** written text again; the user can **continue typing** there.
3. Text inside the popup is **elongated / fully visible** (no ellipsis clip as the primary edit surface).
4. Close on: **click outside**, **Enter**, **Escape**, **blur**, or **~5s idle** without further typing/focus in the popup.
5. After close: the normal under-title field shows the value **truncated** (ellipsis) again. Focusing/tapping the truncated field reopens the popup.

## Implementation

- Reuse `components/auth/AuthExpandableTextField.tsx` — do not invent a one-off per page.
- Overflow detection: `input.scrollWidth > input.clientWidth` on the compact field (not a hard char cap alone).
- Idle close = 5s without interaction in the popup (not literal mouseover).
- Match Festag dark/light popup tokens (`--festag-black-popup`), Aeonik, calm entrance — same spirit as `AuthWorkspacePath` read-only truncate pop, but **editable**.

## Do not

- Clip or ellipsis the active edit text inside the expand popup as the only view of a long value.
- Use middle-dot separators or kickers in related copy.
- Force a full-screen modal for this — keep it a lightweight horizontal expand.

## DE / EN

**DE:** Zu langer Benutzer-/Workspace-Name unter dem Titel → zentriertes Horizontal-Popup zum Weiterschreiben; Schließen per Klick außerhalb, Enter oder 5s Pause; danach wieder abgeschnitten im Normalfeld.

**EN:** Overlong under-title username/workspace → centered horizontal editable popup; close via outside click, Enter, or 5s idle; then truncated again in the compact field.
